Screenshot: makehuman_screenshot01
One factor to take into account whilst exporting MakeHuman Files for Blender
- Pose-animate-skeleton --> choose the basic.json skeleton in order to be able to animate your character in Blender. You are adding the bones to the model!
Export your character as Blender exchange (mhx)

Screenshots: import_makehuman_blender
To be able to import these Blender exchange (mhx) files, you need to activate the correct addon

Screenshots: BlenderHuman
Some images of Blender and the character

Mesh smoothing (in blender, can be don in meshlab also)
- select the mesh
- go to properties panel and select "modifiers" (the blue key)
- add a modifier "Subdivision surface", if not already there
- adapt "method" & "view" params
